def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    # Create index and column codes and levels
    index = data.index
    clocs = [index._get_level_number(i) if isinstance(i, tuple) else i for i in clocs]

    if isinstance(data.columns, MultiIndex):
        result = data.copy()
        for cloc in clocs:
            result = result.unstack(cloc, fill_value=fill_value)
        return result
    else:
        new_data = data.copy()
        columns = new_data.columns
       
        # Create new MultiIndex for unstacked DataFrame
        unstacked_columns = MultiIndex.from_tuples(
            columns, names=[None, *index.names[clocs]])
       
        # Unstack the DataFrame and assign new MultiIndex to columns
        unstacked = new_data.unstack(clocs).reindex(columns=unstacked_columns, fill_value=fill_value)
        return unstacked
